hority on the flowering plants of Concord.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aFlowers in literature. 0aNature in literature. 7aNATURE / Plants / Flowers.2bisacsh1 aAngelo, Ray, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoser, Barry.1 aWisner, Geoff, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311066771440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030022101540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300221015423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300221015/original  a978-3-11-066771-4  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles